{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Silent-success detection (wall-clock timeout + verdict schema-shape + structured refusal-as-content) plus two proven output self-heal tweaks on rebar's already-strong structured.py ladder.\n\n## Why\nA class of failures never raises ŌĆö a safety refusal returned AS the answer (pydantic-ai #5221), an empty/truncated result that looks complete (#5769, #3219), a silent hang (#4681) ŌĆö so exception classification structurally can't see them; they need result validation. Separately, rebar's `structured.py` already implements almost the whole OSS self-heal ladder (native-where-available, tolerant parse, deterministic json-repair BEFORE reask, targeted error-fed reask, fast-fail on truncation/refusal, bounded `OUTPUT_RETRIES=2`) ŌĆö it needs only two cheap, proven additions.\n\n## What\n- Runtime result-validation on every gate call: reuse the existing `check_stop_reason`; add a verdict **schema-shape** check (a parseable verdict object ŌĆö NOT \"non-empty output\", since a clean review legitimately has zero findings). The per-request/tool timeout from story fd1d is the silent-hang backstop.\n- **Truncation-within-a-schema-valid-verdict:** a schema-shape check alone is insufficient ŌĆö a truncated response can still deserialize into a valid-but-stripped verdict. So the check is CONJOINED with the finish-reason signal: a verdict that parses BUT whose `finish_reason`/`stop_reason` indicates `length`/`max_tokens` truncation (already surfaced by `check_stop_reason`) is treated as degraded (routed, not returned as PASS/BLOCK), even though it parsed. Schema-valid AND untruncated is the pass condition.\n- **Refusal-as-content protocol (concrete, distinct from `check_stop_reason`):** `check_stop_reason` already handles the SDK case where `stop_reason/finish_reason == \"refusal\"/\"content_filter\"` with EMPTY parts. The gap (#5221) is a refusal returned as NON-EMPTY content while the provider signals a filter out-of-band. Detection rule: flag refusal-as-content when the response carries non-empty text parts AND `provider_details`/`incomplete_details.reason == \"content_filter\"` (OpenAI Responses) OR the Anthropic `stop_reason` indicates refusal despite text ŌĆö i.e. key on the STRUCTURED provider signal, never a regex over the answer text (which false-fires on tickets/diffs discussing safety). A detected refusal-as-content is routed through story 30ff's SHARED `LLMOutcome` construction (it produces an `LLMOutcome` with `resolution_class = CHANGE_INPUT` + a sanitized diagnostic via the same helper the exception path uses) ŌĆö NOT an independent second routing path ŌĆö so field naming, sanitization, and diagnostic structure are identical whether the disposition came from an exception or from result-validation. Surfaced via `coverage`, not returned as a PASS/BLOCK verdict. (Handoff interface: 30ff exposes the `LLMOutcome` constructor + sanitizer that 978d calls.)\n- Output self-heal in `src/rebar/llm/structured.py` (EXPLICIT deltas vs current code, both confirmed absent today): (1) `structured.py:154` currently calls `repair_json(cand, return_objects=True)` WITHOUT a `schema=` arg ŌĆö add `schema=<model>` for schema-guided deterministic repair before any LLM reask. The pinned `json-repair` exposes `schema=` + `schema_repair_mode` (verified: `repair_json` params include `schema`), so the consumer interface is present; AC confirms the installed version accepts it; (2) `runner.py:490`'s reask currently sends `instructions + schema_hint + \"your previous reply could not be parsed ({exc})\"` but NOT the raw prior output ŌĆö add a bounded snippet of the model's faulty prior reply (`str(result.output)`, truncated) so the model can diff its own mistake (the LangChain `RetryWithErrorOutputParser` / Instructor pattern). Neither is present today; these are genuine additions, not re-statements of existing layers.\n- **Schema coordination:** the verdict schema-shape check validates against the verdict schema as OWNED by story 2eca (which adds `resolution_class`/`diagnostic`). This story does NOT edit the verdict JSON schemas ŌĆö it consumes them; if it lands before 2eca, it checks the pre-existing shape and 2eca's additive fields do not break it.\n\n## Scope\n- Runtime checks + the two `structured.py` tweaks.\n- NOT in scope: a second-interpreter \"fixer\" LLM (`structured.py` explicitly rejects it as an anti-pattern; keep that stance); verdict-schema edits (owned by story 2eca).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Refusal-as-content (via structured signal) and empty/truncated-looks-complete are detected and routed, not returned as a PASS/BLOCK verdict.\n- [ ] A verdict schema-shape check replaces any \"non-empty output\" heuristic; a zero-finding clean review still passes (explicit test).\n- [ ] `json_repair` is called with `schema=<model>`; the targeted reask includes the bounded faulty prior output.\n- [ ] No second-LLM fixer is introduced; no verdict-schema files are edited by this story.\n- [ ] RED silent-success cases flip GREEN; `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `src/rebar/llm/structured.py`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`, the gate verdict-finalization path (read-only on `src/rebar/schemas/*`).\n\n## Verified library behavior (experiment log ŌĆö pydantic-ai 1.107.0, offline)\nACTUAL captured output (no billable call):\n```\nModelResponse fields: [parts, usage, model_name, timestamp, kind, provider_name, provider_url,\n                       provider_details, provider_response_id, finish_reason, run_id, ...]\n  -> finish_reason present (truncation/refusal signal, read by structured.check_stop_reason)\n  -> provider_details present (the STRUCTURED out-of-band filter signal drake keys on, NOT a regex)\nrebar structured.check_stop_reason(stop_reason: str | None) -> None   (reused for the truncation conjunction)\n```\nSo the refusal-as-content detection keys on the structured provider signal (finish_reason +\nprovider_details), never a regex over answer text; and the truncation conjunction reuses the existing\ncheck_stop_reason. A detected silent-success is routed through story mamba's shared LLMOutcome\n(resolution_class=CHANGE_INPUT + sanitized diagnostic) ŌĆö one routing path, not a second. These are\npydantic-ai LIBRARY response fields, not rebar symbols (bug succinct-formable-kite: repo-absence !=\nnon-existence). RED baseline (arawana, committed) pins today: canned content_filter/length finish_reason\n-> UnretryableOutputError; text mode does NOT read finish_reason (the silent-success gap drake closes)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783645096218209001,"uuid":"2311fb94-9058-455b-9e11-e727ab4c68c1"}